        Inaccurate risk estimation and over-prescription of
        risk-reducing therapies can also have economic
        consequences. Cost-effectiveness analyses suggest that the
        cost per life-year saved and total costs rise dramatically
        as treatment is extended to lower-risk <ENAMEX TYPE="PER_DESC">patients</ENAMEX>. [ <TIMEX TYPE="DATE">18</TIMEX> ]
        Accurate risk assessment is crucial for making rationale
